# ❓ Why does Dijkstra fail for negative weights?

Dijkstra assumes:

```text
Once shortest distance is finalized, it never changes.
```

This assumption breaks when negative edges exist.

A negative edge may later produce a smaller distance.

So Dijkstra can produce incorrect answers for graphs containing negative edge weights.

